values:
We are back home after spending Christmas with the evil in-laws.&nbsp; I didn't take a drink or get arrested, so all in all, I guess it was a successful trip.&nbsp; :)&nbsp; 

The Pug Brothers stayed with Dave the St. Bernard and his people.&nbsp; They were overjoyed at first to see us, but are now sulking and acting as if they had been abandoned.&nbsp; Fat Boy is favoring his right hind leg a bit.&nbsp; I'm not sure what happpened, probably Dave sat on him or some other play got out of hand.

I'm wondering now if having them so friendly with such a big (ok, huge) dog was a mistake.&nbsp; They seem to have lost all fear of bigger dogs and will often get right up in their faces in an attempt to initiate play (I guess).&nbsp; They seem more timid around the smaller, yippy hyper-active type dogs.

We are having Christmas with Cop-Son, his wife Christi and my grandson Mini-Bob tonight.&nbsp; Preacher-Son will also be there.&nbsp;
